Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.22,0:12:24.26,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,How is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.54,0:12:29.03,main,MERCHANT B,0,0,0,,She's not gonna make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.43,0:12:33.24,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Shit. Fine, let's move her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.73,0:12:47.37,main,MERCHANTS,0,0,0,,Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.96,0:12:50.70,main,EINAR,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.88,0:13:04.26,main,EINAR,0,0,0,,Hey, what the hell was that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.26,0:13:05.93,main,EINAR,0,0,0,,You didn't need to throw her overboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.80,0:13:13.06,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,All right, you're not swollen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:17.02,main,MERCHANT B,0,0,0,,We're handing out blankets.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.02,0:13:19.34,main,MERCHANT B,0,0,0,,Keep yourselves warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.08,0:13:22.64,main,MERCHANT B,0,0,0,,We paid a fortune for you lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.64,0:13:25.65,main,MERCHANT B,0,0,0,,Don't go getting sick without our say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.36,0:13:29.45,main,MERCHANT B,0,0,0,,At the very least, stay healthy \Nuntil we find a buyer for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.45,0:13:30.50,main,MERCHANT B,0,0,0,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.54,0:13:35.18,main,MERCHANT B,0,0,0,,Come on, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.18,0:13:36.66,main,MERCHANT B,0,0,0,,Take in that sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.47,0:14:07.88,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,That's right. I have to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.92,0:14:22.43,main,MERCHANT D,0,0,0,,Don't skip the liquor. \NIt'll improve your color.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.28,0:14:26.59,main,MERCHANT C,0,0,0,,Clean every nook and cranny, \Nespecially your heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.11,0:14:29.11,main,MERCHANT C,0,0,0,,Check each other for lice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.68,0:14:36.12,main,WOMAN B,0,0,0,,How's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.21,0:14:38.91,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Hair's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.91,0:14:41.48,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Could you do her makeup \Nso she looks a little younger?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.41,0:14:59.74,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Well? Pretty good selection \Nthis time, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.30,0:15:02.29,main,CUSTOMER A,0,0,0,,All second-rate crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.29,0:15:03.84,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,There you go again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.84,0:15:05.78,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,You won't find anything better than ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.17,0:15:12.15,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,That's right. I can't stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.00,0:15:16.74,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,I'll run away. \NAs long as I survive, I can try again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.46,0:15:41.06,main,WOMAN C,0,0,0,,Hup...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.76,0:15:45.19,main,WOMAN C,0,0,0,,Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.28,0:15:47.34,main,EINAR,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.34,0:15:55.76,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Hey, Einar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.64,0:15:59.27,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,You still don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.00,0:16:10.81,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Listen closely, slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.77,0:16:14.62,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Your homes are far, far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.62,0:16:17.15,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,No matter how much you struggle, \Nyou're never getting back to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.15,0:16:22.00,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,And naturally, \Nnobody's gonna help you escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.36,0:16:28.73,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Because you're outsiders \Nand penniless slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.45,0:16:32.92,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Find a good master \Nand serve him as best you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.56,0:16:37.68,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,You'll eat way better than if you \Nrun away and end up a beggar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.03,0:16:41.93,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Before you go running off on adventures, \Nthink real hard about which is better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:45.27,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,You got that, Einar?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.29,0:17:05.06,main,EINAR,0,0,0,,I have to live...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.85,0:17:20.88,main,CUSTOMER B,0,0,0,,Well, he's not bad, but have you \Ngot any boys with a cuter face?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.88,0:17:22.47,main,MERCHANT D,0,0,0,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.47,0:17:26.19,main,MERCHANT D,0,0,0,,In that case, we've got some \Nspecial products for you to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.19,0:17:29.23,main,CUSTOMER B,0,0,0,,Oh, really? How exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.23,0:17:32.17,main,MERCHANT D,0,0,0,,I'm sure you'll find them satisfactory.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.70,0:17:39.29,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,They're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.42,0:17:44.22,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,Even if I blindly ran away, \NI wouldn't know where I was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.89,0:17:46.90,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,And besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.40,0:17:55.32,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,I don't have anywhere to go back to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.51,0:18:02.31,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,As long as I obediently serve \Nsome master somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.55,0:18:08.28,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, you sure are lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.28,0:18:10.52,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,We just got a huge batch in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.52,0:18:11.86,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Look, that's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.23,0:18:16.49,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Isn't he the one you're looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.93,0:18:45.47,main,LEIF,0,0,0,,He looks nothing like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.47,0:18:47.77,main,LEIF,0,0,0,,He's not blond {\i1}or{\i0} small!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.77,0:18:51.06,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,Huh? Now that I get a better look, \NI guess that's not him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.48,0:18:54.08,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,That aside, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.08,0:18:56.56,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,He's strong and tough. If you buy him now—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.56,0:19:00.95,main,LEIF,0,0,0,,I told you, I'm not here to buy a worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.36,0:19:04.03,main,LEIF,0,0,0,,All I want is to free my relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.03,0:19:07.45,main,LEIF,0,0,0,,I'm certain he came to this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.83,0:19:09.77,main,LEIF,0,0,0,,Blond and small...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.77,0:19:11.24,main,LEIF,0,0,0,,His name is Thorfinn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.24,0:19:14.34,main,LEIF,0,0,0,,You really have no idea where he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.89,0:19:23.31,main,LEIF,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.11,0:19:27.40,main,LEIF,0,0,0,,And sorry to have bothered you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.40,0:19:30.44,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,No problem. Come again soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.77,0:19:34.74,main,MERCHANT A,0,0,0,,He's never gonna find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.68,0:19:42.25,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,So he's walking around \Nlooking for his relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.83,0:19:50.34,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,Whoever he's looking for is one lucky guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.12,0:19:56.49,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,You there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.20,0:20:04.73,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,Can you speak? Let me see your teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.27,0:20:19.50,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.93,0:20:21.76,main,EINAR,0,0,0,,Einar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.76,0:20:24.14,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,Where are you from? What did you do before?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.57,0:20:26.80,main,EINAR,0,0,0,,I was a farmer in Northern England.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.42,0:20:28.68,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.32,0:20:39.00,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,What do you say, Einar?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.00,0:20:41.42,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,Would you like to help out on my farm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.48,0:20:50.90,main,EINAR,0,0,0,,A farm...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.21,0:21:16.33,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,Einar, over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.61,0:21:22.91,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,All of my people are at work now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.91,0:21:25.90,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,I'll introduce you to them at dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.90,0:21:26.92,main,EINAR,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.37,0:21:31.08,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,But first, take a look at my farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.58,0:22:07.11,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,Hey, Mom. Was that really true?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.52,0:22:14.73,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,Live or die, I'll never be free again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.43,0:22:21.18,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,You still think I haven't lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.32,0:22:46.98,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,My family was taken from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.52,0:22:50.94,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,I lost my home. I lost everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.79,0:22:56.81,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,I didn't even know \Nwhat the point of living was anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.94,0:23:09.32,main,KETIL,0,0,0,,Thorfinn, it's me. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.48,0:23:30.78,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,"I'll be bought by a good master \Nand do my best to serve him."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.40,0:23:36.04,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,"As long as I'm an obedient slave, \NI won't starve."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.64,0:23:40.70,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,I was beginning to think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.12,0:23:42.62,main,EINAR,0,0,0,,Thorfinn...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.77,0:23:55.99,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.21,0:24:03.10,italics,EINAR,0,0,0,,how Thorfinn and I met.
